          <li><b>Cleaning of the Condenser Coils: </b>Dirt and dust can accumulate on the condenser coils, leading to inefficient heat dissipation and increased energy consumption. Regular cleaning helps maintain performance and energy efficiency.</li>
          <li><b>Checking and Cleaning the Fan and Motor: </b>Ensuring that the fan and its motor are functioning correctly is vital for maintaining airflow and temperature consistency within the cooler.</li>
          <li><b>Inspecting and Sealing the Door Gaskets: </b>orn or damaged door gaskets can lead to air leaks, which compromise the internal temperature stability. Inspecting and replacing these as necessary is a key maintenance task.</li>
