          <li><b>Inspecting the Electrical Connections: </b>Loose or corroded electrical connections can lead to power issues. Tightening and cleaning these connections ensures reliable operation.</li>
          <li><b>Refrigerant Level Check: </b>Ensuring that the refrigerant level is adequate is crucial for the proper functioning of the cooling system. If the levels are low, a leak test and recharge may be required.</li>
          <li><b>Defrost Function Check: </b>For coolers with a defrost cycle, verifying that this function works correctly is important to prevent frost buildup.</li>
          <li><b>Overall System Performance Check: </b>This involves running the cooler to ensure all components are working harmoniously and efficiently.</li>
          <li><b>Cleaning Interior and Exterior: </b>Besides technical aspects, the physical cleaning of both the interior and exterior of the wine cooler is performed to maintain aesthetic appeal and functional integrity.</li>
