            <li>Clean the Condenser Coils: Over time, the condenser coils of wine coolers can accumulate dust and debris, which can impair their ability to cool efficiently. Clean these coils with a brush or a vacuum to improve performance.</li>
            <li>Check the Thermostat: If your wine cooler is running but not reaching the desired temperature, the thermostat might need adjustment or replacement. Make sure it is set correctly, and if adjusting does not help, consider contacting a professional for repair.</li>
            <li>Look for Refrigerant Leaks: If you suspect a refrigerant leak (evidenced by ice buildup in parts of the cooler where it shouldn't be or a noticeable decrease in cooling efficiency), this is a job for a professional. Refrigerant issues require specialized knowledge and tools for safe handling and disposal.</li>
